# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Blog admin store  (why admin changes weren't showing on /blog — read this)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The admin panel (/admin/blogs) saves posts to a CANONICAL store that the public
# /blog + /blog/[slug] pages read. The backend is chosen automatically:
#
#  • PERSISTENT SERVER — local `next dev`, or a self-hosted / WINDOWS SERVER
#    running `next build && next start`: leave the KV vars below BLANK. Posts are
#    saved to public/data/blogs.json on disk and served from there. No setup —
#    admin changes are visible on /blog immediately.
#
#  • SERVERLESS / READ-ONLY FS — Vercel, Netlify, etc.: the filesystem is
#    read-only + ephemeral, so file writes are lost. You MUST point to a network
#    KV store. Create a free Vercel KV / Upstash Redis database (Vercel: Storage
#    → Create Database → KV; it auto-adds the two vars below to the project).
#    Once set, admin changes persist and appear on /blog on every host.
#
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
# (Upstash direct also works — these aliases are accepted too:)
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# Password/token gating the /admin panel and the blog write API. Set the SAME
# value in both (client-visible + server). Defaults to "kaizen-admin-2026".
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
# ADMIN_TOKEN=

# ─── Contact form (Resend email + Turnstile captcha) — see src/app/api ─────────
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# CONTACT_TO=
# CONTACT_FROM=
# CAPTCHA_SECRET=
